    %h2 Code.org District Partner Program
    %p As AI and emerging technologies transform nearly every aspect of our lives, Code.org is leading a movement to ensure that K-12 students are equipped to adapt to the realities of a rapidly evolving knowledge economy. For more than a decade, Code.org has partnered with educators to advocate for not just policy change, but the resources necessary to expand access to high quality computer science curriculum and professional learning experiences.
    %p District leaders around the country can now partner with Code.org directly, at no cost to:
    %ul
      %li Prepare students to thrive in a rapidly evolving world of work
      %li Boost access to engaging STEM courses and pathways
      %li Invest in teachers through high-quality professional learning experiences
      %li Tap into the energy, aspirations, and potential of all students to close equity gaps in computer science education and career pathways
      %li Align with the education-to-workforce priorities of employers and policymakers
